#BTC UPDATE :

As for wave analysis, on the H1 graph, we don't see the finished 5th wave and divergence, which could unequivocally tell about the end of a local fall.
At the same time, the fall from $ 4130 to $ 3510 occurred without normal kickbacks, which is normal for stretching in waves, but indicates a future correction. After the end of the local fall in the wave (5 in blue), I expect growth in the form of a correction of this fall.
Some traders expect a general increase after this fall to 4200$-4500$
Therefore, Im more inclined to think that this will be a fall correction, which will reach 0.38 ($ 3,750) / 0.50 ($ 3,820) - 0.62 ($ 3,900) Fibbo levels, after which we will continue to fall and refresh the lows.
At the same time, this scenario will be locally incorrect if the price goes above $ 4000-4130.
It's better to not enter on a short on this level the downward movement may not be large, in which case the risk will not correspond to the profit.
